# CODEOWNERS — required reviewers for every PR on this repo.
#
# Every path below maps to one or more GitHub handles. When a PR touches
# a matching file, GitHub automatically requests a review from the
# corresponding owner, and the branch-protection rule on `main` blocks
# merge until at least one CODEOWNER approves.
#
# References:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Notes for contributors:
#   * You do NOT need to be a CODEOWNER to open a PR.
#   * You DO need a CODEOWNER's approval for it to merge.
#   * If a CODEOWNER is the PR author, an additional reviewer is still
#     required (configured via branch protection: dismiss stale reviews
#     + require approval from someone other than the author).

